<div id="review_1289371670" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1289371670" />
    <a title="Yasmine Abdelhai" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12076193-yasmine-abdelhai"><img alt="Yasmine Abdelhai" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1424021077p2/12076193.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1289371670?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Yasmine Abdelhai" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Yasmine Abdelhai" href="/user/show/12076193-yasmine-abdelhai">Yasmine Abdelhai</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1289371670" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17891793738497547301">unnecessary elboration in regards to the abu graham prison incidents and the stanford prison experiment. The book doesn&apos;t not prove a theory or give an understanding of the process of becoming evil. that being said chapter 15, and 16 went breifly over the psychological/ behavioural factors that makes people turn bad and then also breifly how should we deal with evil people when we are faced with situation where they try to dehumanize us etc. but then in the chapter after that he goes and gives e</span>
  <span id="freeText17891793738497547301" style="display:none">unnecessary elboration in regards to the abu graham prison incidents and the stanford prison experiment. The book doesn't not prove a theory or give an understanding of the process of becoming evil. that being said chapter 15, and 16 went breifly over the psychological/ behavioural factors that makes people turn bad and then also breifly how should we deal with evil people when we are faced with situation where they try to dehumanize us etc. but then in the chapter after that he goes and gives examples of people who stood in the face of evil and they were some how punished by the society latter on! :D <br />i was right all along Human beings are not so human after all<br />we are doomed ! :D</span>
